                <h1>The Evolution of Religion: A Brief History</h1>
                <p>The history of religion traces humanity's quest to understand the divine and find meaning in life. From ancient polytheism to modern monotheistic faiths, religious practices have shaped cultures and societies. Major religions like Hinduism, Judaism, Buddhism, Christianity, and Islam have evolved, influencing ethical systems, art, and civilization itself.</p>
